<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-29-0003 </DOCNO><TEXT>The depletion of cheap fossil fuels is a problem which confronts modernsociety. This book strongly advocates the use of the earth's renewableenergy resources to solve this problem. In a readable style the authordetails the uses of biomass, solar, wind, water, and geothermal energy,and reports on technologies that are currently using these energy sources.Among the ideas cited are man-made solar salt ponds and vertical axishydroturbines that operate on solar power. Technologies for many of therenewable resources described were developed and tested in California.</TEXT></DOC>